SENATE BILL 700
A2 6lr3223
CF HB 754
By: Wicomico County Senators
Introduced and read first time: February 6, 2026
Assigned to: Finance
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Wicomico County – Alcoholic Beverages – Class B (Golf Course) License –
3 Hours of Sale
4 FOR the purpose of altering the hours during which a holder of a Class B beer, wine, and
5 liquor (golf course) license in Wicomico County may sell alcoholic beverages; and
6 generally relating to alcoholic beverages licenses in Wicomico County.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
8 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
9 Section 32–102
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
13 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
14 Section 32–1003
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – Alcoholic Beverages and Cannabis
20 32–102
21 This title applies only in Wicomico County.
22 32–1003.
23 (a) There is a Class B beer, wine, and liquor (golf course) license.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *sb0700*

2 SENATE BILL 700
1 (b) The Board of License Commissioners may issue the license for the use of a golf
2 course or organization that:
3 (1) is open to the public;
4 (2) is operated for profit;
5 (3) owns real estate in the county; and
6 (4) has a golf course with a minimum of 18 holes.
7 (c) (1) The license holder may sell beer, wine, and liquor for consumption on
8 the land and in the buildings, including the clubhouse, used for golfing purposes.
9 (2) A patron need not be seated to be served.
10 (d) A holder of the license may sell beer, wine, and liquor:
11 (1) on Monday through Saturday, from [10 a.m.] 7 A.M. to 2 a.m. the
12 following day; and
13 (2) on Sunday, from [10 a.m.] 7 A.M. to midnight.
14 (e) The annual license fee is $2,200.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
16 1, 2026.

